cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper deals with natural language generation using LSTM networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also analyzes the statistical structure of the generated language, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of LSTM networks also involves neural networks (cs.NE) and the analysis of statistical features involves information theory (cs.SD).
